SIMPLE: plumper
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plumper
<hw>Plump"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, plumps or swells out something else; hence, something
carried in the mouth to distend the cheeks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(English Elections)</fld> <def>A vote given to one
candidate only, when two or more are to be elected, thus giving him the
advantage over the others. A person who gives his vote thus is said to
<xex>plump</xex>, or to <xex>plump</xex> his vote.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A voter who plumps his vote.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A downright, unqualified lie.</def> <mark>[Colloq.
or Low]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plumply</ent>⟦br⟧
